The paper deals with network coding in multicast networks, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the construction of multicast networks, which can be seen as a problem in distributed systems (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the properties of finite fields, which is a topic in algebraic coding theory (cs.SI) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC).
